{{Other uses2|Brian Stanley}}{{Infobox academic|name=Brian Stanley|nationality=British|occupation=Scholar of [[Missiologist|missions]] [[Church history|history]]|known_for=History of [[world Christianity]]|discipline=[[Missiology|Missions study]], [[Church history]]|workplaces=[[University of Cambridge]], [[University of Edinburgh]]|alma_mater=[[University of Cambridge]]}}
{{Use dmy dates|date=December 2016}}
{{Use British English|date=December 2016}}
Professor '''Brian Stanley''' is a British historian, best known for his works in the history of [[Christian missions]] and [[world Christianity]].

== Biography ==
He received his BA, MA, and PhD degrees in history from [[University of Cambridge]], and has taught in theological colleges in London, Bristol, and Cambridge.

From 1996 to 2001, he was director of the Currents in World Christianity Project in the University of Cambridge, where he was a fellow of [[St Edmund's College, Cambridge|St Edmund's College]] before joining the faculty at the [[University of Edinburgh]] in January 2009. He is currently Professor of [[World Christianity]] and Director for the [[Centre for the Study of World Christianity]] at the [[New College, Edinburgh|School of Divinity]] in the University of Edinburgh.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.ed.ac.uk/profile/brian-stanley|title=Professor Brian Stanley|last=|first=|date=|website=School of Divinity, University of Edinburgh|publisher=|accessdate=29 October 2016}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.baylorisr.org/scholars/s/brian-stanley/|title = Brian Stanley | website =Baylor Institute for Studies of Religion| accessdate =1 September 2015}}</ref>

He is also currently the chief editor of the academic journal ''[[Studies in World Christianity]]''<ref>{{cite web | url=http://www.euppublishing.com/page/swc/editorialBoard|title=Editorial Board | website = Edinburgh University Press|accessdate = 2 September 2015}}</ref> and part of the editorial board of ''[[The Journal of Ecclesiastical History]].''<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.cambridge.org/core/journals/journal-of-ecclesiastical-history/information/editorial-board|title=Editorial board|last=|first=|date=|website=Cambridge University Press|publisher=|access-date=7 October 2016}}</ref> Along with Robert Eric Frykenberg, Stanley is co-editor of the Studies in the History of Christian Missions book series from the [[William B. Eerdmans Publishing Company]].<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.eerdmans.com/Products/CategoryCenter.aspx?CategoryId=SE!SHCM|title=Studies in the History of Christian Missions|last=|first=|date=|website=Wm. B. Eerdmans|publisher=|access-date=7 October 2016}}</ref>

