'''Chimid Balzanov''' was a Buddhist priest of [[Kalmyk people|Kalmyk]] origin who was elected religious head of the Kalmyks by leaders of the Kalmyk community at a Kalmyk Congress, which assembled after the [[February Revolution]] on March 25, 1917 and on July 23–25, 1917 to discuss spiritual, cultural and economic issues.

