The '''Masjid-e-Hindan''' ({{lang-fa|مسجد هندان}}, "Mosque of the Indians") is a Sikh [[gurdwara]] in Tehran, Iran.<ref>[http://www.sikhreview.org/june2001/diary.htm Prime Minister pays homage at Teheran Gurdwara] {{webarchive|url=https://web.archive.org/web/20110718101542/http://www.sikhreview.org/june2001/diary.htm |date=2011-07-18 }}. ''Sikh Review'', June 2001</ref>  The gurdwara serves Tehran's very small [[Sikhism in Iran|Sikh community]]. Despite its name, the complex is not an Islamic Mosque, and is given due to the Muslim majority in Iran.

