{{EngvarB|date=June 2016}} {{Use dmy dates|date=June 2016}} {{About|the Roman Catholic bishop|the current Anglican bishop|Anglican Bishop of Leeds}} {{Infobox Bishopric |border = catholic |font_color = black |bishopric = [[Leeds]] |coatofarms = |image = <!-- Image of the current incumbent --> |incumbent = [[Marcus Stock]] |province = [[Province of Liverpool|Liverpool]] |diocese = [[Roman Catholic Diocese of Leeds|Leeds]] |cathedral = [[Leeds Cathedral]] |first_bishop = [[Robert Cornthwaite (bishop)|Robert Cornthwaite]] |date = 20 December 1878 |website = [http://www.dioceseofleeds.org.uk/d_bishop/personalinfo.php Bishop of Leeds] }}
The '''Bishop of Leeds''' is the [[Ordinary (officer)|Ordinary]] of the [[Roman Catholic Diocese of Leeds]] in the [[Province of Liverpool]], England.<ref name=dleed>{{Catholic-hierarchy|diocese|dleed|Diocese of Leeds|14 August 2011}}</ref>
The [[Vicariate Apostolic]] of the [[Yorkshire]] District was elevated to diocese status as the [[Diocese of Beverley]] on 29 September 1850, which was suppressed on 20 December 1878 and its area was divided into the dioceses of [[Roman Catholic Diocese of Leeds|Leeds]] and [[Roman Catholic Diocese of Middlesbrough|Middlesbrough]].
The Diocese of Leeds covers an area of {{convert|4075|km2|sqmi|-2|abbr=on}} and consists of the County of [[West Yorkshire]], together parts of the counties of the [[East Riding of Yorkshire]], [[North Yorkshire]], [[Greater Manchester]], [[Lancashire]], and [[Cumbria]].<ref name=dleed/> The [[Episcopal see|see]] is in the city of Leeds where the [[Cathedra|bishop's seat]] is located at the [[Leeds Cathedral|Cathedral Church of Saint Anne]], Cookridge Street.<ref name=dleed/>
On 15 September 2014, Pope Francis appointed Monsignor Marcus Stock, at the time, the General Secretary of the Bishops' Conference, as the 10th Bishop of Leeds.<ref>[http://en.radiovaticana.va/news/2014/09/15/pope_appoints_msgr_marcus_stock_to_diocese_of_leeds_uk/1106539 Pope appoints Msgr. Marcus Stock to Diocese of Leeds UK] from ''[[Vatican Radio]]'' retrieved 15 September 2015</ref> He was consecrated as Bishop on 13 November 2014.<ref name=mstock/>
